orders['days_to_carrier'] = (orders['order_delivered_carrier_date'] - orders['order_purchase_timestamp']).dt.total_seconds() / (24 * 60 * 60)
orders['days_to_customer'] = (orders['order_delivered_customer_date'] - orders['order_purchase_timestamp']).dt.total_seconds() / (24 * 60 * 60)

# 0100
orders_delivery = orders[
    (orders['days_to_customer'] > 0) &
    (orders['days_to_customer'] < 100) &
    (orders['order_status'] == 'delivered')
].copy()

#

print("\n3-2")
orders['order_month'] = orders['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.month_name()

    index=orders['order_month'],
    columns=orders['order_status'],
    normalize='index'
) * 100
print(monthly_status.round(2).reindex(month_order)['canceled'])

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
if 'canceled' in monthly_status.columns:
    plt.plot(monthly_status.reindex(month_order).index,
             monthly_status.reindex(month_order)['canceled'],

    plt.title(' (Monthly Cancellation Rate)',fontproperties=mpl.font_manager.FontProperties(fname='/usr/share/fonts/truetype/fonts-japanese-gothic.ttf'), fontsize=15)
